# af_packet doesn't auto-load via the kernel's own request_module() the
# first time something opens an AF_PACKET socket — both LLDP and the
# DHCPv4 client's initial DISCOVER (sent before the interface has an IP,
# so it must go out over a raw packet socket) silently never fire without
# it. Load it explicitly, before systemd-networkd starts.
af_packet
